  <prompt>
    <goal>Create docs/architecture/rag-architecture.md — document the RAG pipeline end-to-end including text chunking, embedding generation and cache, Azure AI Search integration, and scheduled indexing</goal>
    <context>The Spaarke platform implements a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline that ingests documents from SharePoint Embedded, chunks text, generates embeddings via Azure OpenAI, indexes into Azure AI Search, and retrieves context for AI tool responses. No architecture document captures this pipeline end-to-end.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use /docs-architecture skill structure
      - Source ALL content from actual code — do not invent RAG components
      - Document the full pipeline: ingest → chunk → embed → index → retrieve → augment
      - Include text chunking strategy (chunk size, overlap, metadata preservation)
      - Document embedding generation and caching strategy
      - Map Azure AI Search index schema and query patterns
      - Include scheduled indexing jobs and triggers
      - Cite source files for every pipeline stage
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
